36
00:02:40,325 --> 00:02:49,930
[SPEAKER_14]: And so the way this process works is first, any member of the board can nominate the chair for the next calendar year.

37
00:02:52,131 --> 00:02:54,112
[SPEAKER_14]: That nomination would have to be seconded.

38
00:02:55,392 --> 00:03:00,094
[SPEAKER_14]: The person nominated would have to accept once all nominations have been made.

39
00:03:01,928 --> 00:03:09,994
[SPEAKER_14]: then we would vote on the member, basically vote for whomever we would like the chair to be.

40
00:03:10,554 --> 00:03:17,179
[SPEAKER_14]: Dennis is our clerk and is on staff, and so we won't be voting on a clerk.

41
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:24,824
[SPEAKER_14]: All right, so the chair awaits a nomination, or the acting chair awaits a nomination.

42
00:03:29,461 --> 00:03:33,883
[SPEAKER_03]: I'd like to nominate Mike Caldera to serve as Zoning Board of Appeals Chair.

43
