[SPEAKER_05]: But it allows us to create a cut-through, or I'm sorry, not a cut-through, a drop-off or a lay-by in this area.

342
00:37:16,584 --> 00:37:27,067
[SPEAKER_05]: So our plan is to carve, and we'll show this obviously in the plan set, carve out a small inset in this area to allow for short-term loading and unloading.

343
00:37:27,807 --> 00:37:28,867
[SPEAKER_05]: We know that there can be

344
00:37:29,855 --> 00:37:41,321
[SPEAKER_05]: If it's a move-in that's a van size, it can certainly fit within the garage, then we can manage that process with the resident and their move-in, and that'd be best case scenario.

345
00:37:41,641 --> 00:37:56,127
[SPEAKER_05]: But if we have a larger truck that is hard to maneuver and get in and out of the garage, we'll have a lay-by area here that can be obviously reserved on a time schedule with our management team to make sure that a moving truck can be in and out of there efficiently.

346
00:37:57,825 --> 00:38:04,649
[SPEAKER_05]: And that's something we've done in Metro West in a couple of different communities and feel like it will work well here.

347
00:38:04,689 --> 00:38:18,897
[SPEAKER_05]: And before we put pen to paper on it, it's something we talked about with our transportation engineer, Mr. Dirk, as well, to make sure that works from a site logistics and circulation standpoint.

348
00:38:21,471 --> 00:38:28,116
[SPEAKER_04]: On that issue, Mr. Alexander, is there a freight elevator or is it just people would be moving in the regular elevators?

349
00:38:29,237 --> 00:38:31,338
[SPEAKER_05]: So we generally can dictate.

350
00:38:31,438 --> 00:38:32,439
[SPEAKER_05]: That's a great question.

351
00:38:33,180 --> 00:38:35,261
[SPEAKER_05]: We have we'll do a couple of things.

352
00:38:35,401 --> 00:38:44,608
[SPEAKER_05]: We have what we've gone to actually more recently is an increased ceiling height on on multiple elevators.

353
00:38:45,728 --> 00:38:50,652
[SPEAKER_05]: We in the past, we dictated a freight elevator and then you always get different, you know,

354
00:38:51,185 --> 00:38:56,327
[SPEAKER_05]: shapes and sizes of things that sometimes make their way to the freight elevator and sometimes don't.

355
00:38:57,107 --> 00:39:01,749
[SPEAKER_05]: So we've used an increased height to our elevator cabs in multiple.

356
00:39:01,809 --> 00:39:05,430
[SPEAKER_05]: So we'll probably have one in each building that has that increased height.

357
00:39:05,790 --> 00:39:18,054
[SPEAKER_05]: And then we can, as you are used to seeing, we'll make sure that that elevator is protected and has the sort of hanging protection up for move-ins.

358
00:39:21,657 --> 00:39:29,804
[SPEAKER_05]: So, and I say that because I don't believe it would be a best practice for us to take one of these elevators and just call it freight.

359
00:39:33,146 --> 00:39:37,430
[SPEAKER_03]: Any other questions from the board on this part of the presentation?

